23/07/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul said Tuesday (22 July) that his current visit to the United States would focus on efforts to place Turkish-US relations on a sounder footing. Gul will meet with Vice President Dick Cheney, Secretary of State Colin Powell, National Security Adviser Condoleezza Rice and members of the US Congress. They will focus on Iraq-related issues, including security and the possible deployment of Turkish peacekeepers to Iraq.
In other news, an earthquake measuring 5.2 on the Richter scale hit the western Turkish province of Denizli on Wednesday morning. No casualties were reported, but the quake sent panicked residents into the streets. (Hurriyet, Radikal, Anadolu Agency, AFP - 23/07/03; Anadolu Agency, NTV, AFP - 22/07/03)
